definitions.definition: The broken remains of an object, usually rock or masonry .
A mass or stratum of fragments of rock lying under the alluvium and derived from the neighbouring rock.
The whole of the bran of wheat before it is sorted into pollard , bran, etc.

main_definition: The broken remains of an object, usually rock or masonry .
secondary_definitions: ( geology ) A mass or stratum of fragments of rock lying under the alluvium and derived from the neighbouring rock.
( UK , dialect , in the plural ) The whole of the bran of wheat before it is sorted into pollard , bran, etc.
